title <b>NextGenChat — Agent Message Pipeline</b>\n<size:10>Complete flow from user message → agent streaming response</size>

actor "User" as User
participant "WebApp\n(Next.js)" as Client
participant "Socket.io\n/chat namespace" as SIO
participant "Message\nService" as MsgSvc
database "PostgreSQL" as PG
participant "Agent\nTrigger Svc" as Trigger
queue "BullMQ\n(Redis-backed)" as Queue
participant "Agent\nProcessor Worker" as Worker
participant "Context\nBuilder" as CB
participant "Token\nCounter" as TC
participant "Compaction\nWorker" as CW
participant "LLM\nProvider" as LLM

== 1. User Sends Message ==

User -> Client : types message, presses send
activate Client

Client -> SIO : emit <b>message:send</b>\n{ channelId, content, contentType }
activate SIO

note over SIO
  <b>Zod validation on every socket payload.</b>
  Invalid schema → error emitted back, no processing.
  Auth token verified once on socket handshake —
  not re-validated per event (JWT cached in socket state).
end note

SIO -> MsgSvc : createMessage(channelId, userId, content)
activate MsgSvc

MsgSvc -> PG : INSERT into messages\n{ senderId, senderType: USER, channelId,\n  content, contentType, createdAt }
activate PG
PG --> MsgSvc : message { id, createdAt, ... }
deactivate PG

MsgSvc --> SIO : message record
deactivate MsgSvc

SIO -> SIO : broadcast to room\n<b>channel:{channelId}</b>
SIO --> Client : emit <b>message:new</b>\n(all clients in room receive it)
deactivate Client

note right of Client
  Optimistic UI: message was already
  shown locally when user hit send.
  Server response replaces tempId
  with the real persisted message ID.
end note

== 2. Agent Trigger Detection ==

SIO -> Trigger : checkTriggers(channelId, message)
activate Trigger

note over Trigger
  Rules checked in order:
  1. Is senderType === AGENT? → skip (anti-loop guard)
  2. Does channel have active agents?
  3. Per agent: trigger mode?
     • MENTIONS_ONLY → content includes @agent-name?
     • ALL_MESSAGES  → always trigger
     • DISABLED      → skip
end note

loop for each triggered agent

  Trigger -> Queue : add job <b>agent:process</b>\n{ agentId, channelId, messageId,\n  attempts: 0, timeout: 90000 }
  activate Queue

  note right of Queue
    BullMQ persists job to Redis.
    Config: maxAttempts=3,
    backoff: { type: exponential, delay: 2000ms }
    Job visible to admin in audit log.
  end note

end

deactivate Trigger

== 3. Agent Processor Worker Picks Up Job ==

Queue -> Worker : dequeue <b>agent:process</b>
deactivate Queue
activate Worker

Worker -> PG : SELECT Agent + AgentIdentity\n+ ProviderConfig (encrypted credentials)\nWHERE id = agentId
activate PG
PG --> Worker : agent config + encrypted creds
deactivate PG

Worker -> Worker : decrypt credentials\n(AES-256-GCM, key from ENCRYPTION_KEY env)

note over Worker
  <b>Credentials decrypted IN MEMORY ONLY.</b>
  Never written to any log line.
  Never returned in any API response.
  Decrypted string lives only for the duration
  of this LLM call, then garbage collected.
end note

== 4. Build Context Window ==

Worker -> CB : build(agentId, channelId, triggerMessageId)
activate CB

CB -> PG : SELECT AgentMemory\nWHERE agentId = ? AND scope IN (GLOBAL, CHANNEL)
activate PG
PG --> CB : memory key-value pairs
deactivate PG

CB -> PG : SELECT ConversationSummary\nWHERE channelId = ? AND agentId = ?\nORDER BY createdAt DESC LIMIT 1
activate PG
PG --> CB : summary (or null)
deactivate PG

CB -> PG : SELECT messages FROM channel\nORDER BY createdAt DESC LIMIT 100
activate PG
PG --> CB : candidate message array
deactivate PG

CB -> TC : countTokens(systemPrompt + memory\n+ summary + candidates)
activate TC

note over TC
  <b>Token counting is provider-specific:</b>
  OpenAI / Kimi / OpenRouter:
    tiktoken, cl100k_base encoding
    +4 tokens overhead per message role
  Anthropic:
    POST /v1/messages/count_tokens (exact count)
    Result cached in Redis 60s (hash of msgs as key)
end note

TC --> CB : totalTokenCount
deactivate TC

CB -> CB : compute available budget:\nbudget = contextLimit[model] - 4096

alt totalTokens > budget (OVER BUDGET)

  note over CB
    <b>Compaction needed.</b>
    Current call: use truncated history (most recent messages).
    Async job: summarize the overflow and save for next call.
  end note

  CB -> Queue : enqueue <b>compaction:process</b>\n{ agentId, channelId, overflowMessageIds[] }

  ' Async compaction runs in parallel
  Queue -> CW : dequeue compaction job
  activate CW #FFE0E0

  CW -> PG : fetch overflow messages (full content)
  activate PG
  PG --> CW : messages to summarize
  deactivate PG

  CW -> LLM : complete() — cheap model\n(gpt-4o-mini or claude-haiku)\nPrompt: "Summarize this conversation\nhistory, preserving key facts..."
  activate LLM #FFE8E8
  LLM --> CW : summaryText + tokenCount
  deactivate LLM

  CW -> PG : INSERT ConversationSummary\n{ channelId, agentId, summary,\n  tokenCount, coversFromMsgId,\n  covesToMsgId, createdAt }
  activate PG
  PG --> CW
  deactivate PG
  deactivate CW

  note over CW
    <b>ASYNC — does NOT block current LLM call.</b>
    Current call uses truncated history.
    All future calls for this agent+channel
    will load and use this summary instead.
  end note

  CB --> Worker : context { messages: truncatedHistory,\n  systemPrompt, memory }

else totalTokens <= budget (WITHIN BUDGET)

  CB --> Worker : context { messages: fullHistory,\n  systemPrompt, memory }

end
deactivate CB

== 5. Anthropic Prompt Cache Hints (conditional) ==

opt provider === 'anthropic'
  Worker -> Worker : insert cache_control: { type: "ephemeral" }\nafter last static message\n(system prompt + memory + summary boundary)

  note right of Worker
    <b>Anthropic Prompt Caching:</b>
    Static prefix (system + memory) cached by Anthropic 5min.
    cache_creation_input_tokens = normal price (first call)
    cache_read_input_tokens = ~10% of normal (cache hits)
    Both stored in Message.metadata for cost analytics.
  end note
end

== 6. LLM Streaming Call ==

Worker -> LLM : stream(messages, tools?, maxTokens, temperature)
activate LLM

note over LLM
  <b>Provider-specific streaming:</b>
  OpenAI / Kimi / OpenRouter: SSE "data: {...}" chunks
  Anthropic: SSE "event: content_block_delta" + "data: {...}"
  Tool calls interleaved in stream if agent has approved tools.
  All errors mapped: 429=RATE_LIMITED, 401=AUTH_FAILED,
  5xx=PROVIDER_ERROR → retry with backoff up to 2x.
end note

loop for each streaming token chunk

  LLM --> Worker : StreamChunk { delta: "token...", finishReason: null }
  Worker -> SIO : emit to room channel:{channelId}\n<b>message:stream:chunk</b>\n{ tempId, delta }
  SIO --> Client : real-time token\n(user sees agent typing)

end

LLM --> Worker : StreamChunk { finishReason: "stop",\n  usage: { promptTokens, completionTokens,\n  totalTokens, cachedTokens? } }
deactivate LLM

== 7. Persist Agent Response ==

Worker -> PG : INSERT into messages\n{ senderType: AGENT, channelId,\n  senderId: agentId, content: fullResponse,\n  metadata: { provider, model,\n  promptTokens, completionTokens,\n  cachedTokens, finishReason,\n  toolCalls[] } }
activate PG
PG --> Worker : message { id, createdAt }
deactivate PG

Worker -> SIO : emit to room\n<b>message:stream:end</b>\n{ tempId, finalMessageId, createdAt }
SIO --> Client : replace streaming placeholder\nwith persisted message

note right of Client
  Client swaps the streaming UI element
  (identified by tempId) with the final
  confirmed message record from the server.
  Token usage optionally shown in UI.
end note

== 8. Memory Update ==

opt agent response includes memory operations (via tool calls)

  Worker -> PG : UPSERT into agent_memory\n{ agentId, scope, key, value: JSONB }

  note right of Worker
    <b>Memory size enforced: 50KB per scope.</b>
    Scopes: GLOBAL | CHANNEL | USER
    GLOBAL: persists across all channels
    CHANNEL: per channel context
    USER: per individual user interaction
  end note

end
deactivate Worker

== Error Path ==

note over Worker, LLM
  <b>If job times out (90s) or all retries exhausted:</b>
  1. Emit system message to channel: "⚠ Agent timed out"
  2. Log full error server-side (never in chat message)
  3. Mark BullMQ job as FAILED
  4. Admin can view failed jobs in audit log
  <b>If AUTH_FAILED (401):</b>
  Mark ProviderConfig as invalid,
  emit "🔑 Provider credentials expired" in admin channel.
end note

@enduml


