@startuml ContextWindowManagement

!theme plain
skinparam defaultFontName "Arial"
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam roundcorner 6

skinparam activity {
  BorderColor #2255AA
  BackgroundColor #EAF2FB
  FontColor #111111
  StartColor #228833
  EndColor #AA2222
  DiamondBorderColor #996633
  DiamondBackgroundColor #FFF4E6
  DiamondFontColor #333333
  ArrowColor #444444
}
skinparam swimlane {
  BorderColor #888888
  TitleFontStyle bold
  TitleFontSize 12
}
skinparam note {
  BackgroundColor #FEFEE8
  BorderColor #CCCC66
  FontSize 10
}

title <b>NextGenChat — Context Window Management</b>\n<size:10>3 layers: Token Budgeting → Auto-Compaction → Prompt Caching</size>

|#EAF2FB| **Context Builder** |
|#FFF4E6| **Token Counter** |
|#EAF8EA| **Compaction Worker** |
|#FFF0F8| **LLM Provider** |

|Context Builder|
start

:Load static context from DB:
- **System prompt** (AgentIdentity.systemPrompt)
- **Agent memory** (GLOBAL + CHANNEL scopes)
  — injected as structured text into context;

note right
  <b>Memory scopes:</b>
  GLOBAL — persists across all channels
  CHANNEL — per-channel only
  USER — per individual human user
  <b>Size enforced:</b> 50KB max per scope.
  Exceeding entries: LRU eviction.
end note

:Load latest **ConversationSummary** from DB
(most recent compaction result
for this agentId + channelId pair);

:Fetch candidate messages from DB
— newest first, up to MAX_CANDIDATES (100)
— these may not all fit in budget;

|Token Counter|

:Count tokens in full candidate set:
systemPrompt + memory + summary + messages;

note right
  <b>Per-provider implementation:</b>

  OpenAI / Kimi / OpenRouter:
    tiktoken, cl100k_base encoding
    Manual overhead: +4 tokens per message
    (role name + formatting tokens)
    Fast — runs locally, no API call.

  Anthropic (exact):
    POST /v1/messages/count_tokens
    Returns exact token count from model.
    Result cached in Redis 60s
    using SHA-256(messages) as key
    — prevents redundant API calls.
end note

|Context Builder|

:Compute **available budget**:
budget = contextLimit[model] - RESPONSE_BUFFER
RESPONSE_BUFFER = 4096 tokens (reserved for response);

note right
  <b>Context limits by model:</b>
  gpt-4o, gpt-4o-mini  → 128,000
  gpt-4-turbo          → 128,000
  o1, o3               → 200,000
  claude-opus-4-6      → 200,000
  claude-sonnet-4-6    → 200,000
  kimi-k2-5            → 131,072
  openrouter models    → from model list
                         (cached 1h in Redis)
end note

if (totalTokens <= budget?) then (YES — fits in budget)

  :Use full candidate message set
  — no truncation needed;

else (NO — over budget)

  if (ConversationSummary exists?) then (YES — prior compaction)

    :Replace oldest messages with the summary.
    Add recent messages on top of summary
    until budget is reached;

    if (summary + recent messages still over budget?) then (STILL TOO LARGE)

      :Use summary only +
      most recent N messages that fit;

      note right
        <b>Recursive case:</b>
        Summaries can accumulate over time.
        If summaries themselves overflow:
        summarize-the-summaries.
        Max depth: 3 levels of summarization.
      end note

    else (fits)
      :Use summary + recent messages;
    endif

  else (NO — no summary yet, first compaction)

    :Truncate oldest candidate messages
    until total token count fits in budget;

  endif

  ' Trigger async compaction in parallel
  :Determine overflow message IDs
  (messages that did not fit in budget);

  |Compaction Worker|
  fork
    :Enqueue **compaction:process** BullMQ job
    { agentId, channelId, overflowMessageIds[] };

    note right
      <b>ASYNC — current LLM call is NOT blocked.</b>
      Current call proceeds with truncated context.
      Compaction runs in background.
      Future calls benefit from the summary.
    end note

    :Fetch overflow messages full content from DB;

    :Build summarization prompt:
    "Summarize this conversation history
    concisely, preserving: decisions made,
    key facts, outcomes, unresolved questions.";

    :Call **cheap model** via LLM provider:
    OpenAI agents → gpt-4o-mini
    Anthropic agents → claude-haiku-4-5;

    :Receive summaryText + tokenCount;

    :INSERT ConversationSummary into DB:
    { channelId, agentId,
      summary: summaryText,
      tokenCount,
      coversFromMessageId,
      covesToMessageId,
      createdAt: now() };

    note right
      Next call for this agent+channel
      will load this summary as compressed history.
      summary.tokenCount << original message tokens.
    end note

  fork again
    ' Current call continues with truncated context
    |Context Builder|
    :Continue with truncated context
    (current call uses partial history);
  end fork

endif

' Assemble final message array
|Context Builder|

:Assemble final message array in order:
1. System prompt
2. Agent memory (key-value pairs as text block)
3. ConversationSummary (if used in this call)
4. Recent messages (within budget)
5. Trigger message (ALWAYS last);

' Prompt caching branch
|LLM Provider|

if (provider === 'anthropic'?) then (YES)

  :Insert **cache_control: { type: "ephemeral" }**
  marker after the last static message
  (boundary = after memory, before dynamic history);

  note right
    <b>Anthropic Prompt Caching behavior:</b>

    First call (cache miss):
      cache_creation_input_tokens charged at full price.
      Anthropic stores the prefix (5-min TTL).

    Subsequent calls (cache hit):
      cache_read_input_tokens at ~10% of full price.
      Savings logged to Message.metadata.

    Cache warmth strategy:
      If agent is active, re-request every 4 minutes
      to reset the 5-min TTL (configurable).

    Admin dashboard shows:
      hit rate, creation cost, read cost, savings.
  end note

else (OpenAI / Kimi / OpenRouter)

  note right
    <b>OpenAI implicit prefix caching:</b>
    No API needed — OpenAI caches matching
    prompt prefixes automatically.
    Keep system prompt + memory FIRST and STABLE
    between requests to maximize cache hits.
    Track cached_tokens from usage response.
    Stored in Message.metadata for analytics.
  end note

endif

:Call **LLMProvider.stream()** or .complete()
with assembled, budget-validated context;

:Receive response + usage stats:
{ promptTokens, completionTokens,
  totalTokens, cachedTokens? };

:Store usage in **Message.metadata JSONB**:
{ provider, model, promptTokens,
  completionTokens, cachedTokens,
  finishReason, toolCalls[] };

note right
  <b>Analytics available at:</b>
  GET /agents/:id/context-stats
  Returns:
  • Avg tokens/request (prompt + completion)
  • Cache hit rate (Anthropic)
  • Compaction count + history
  • Estimated cost savings from caching
end note

if (agent signals memory operations via tool?) then (YES)

  :UPSERT AgentMemory rows in DB
  (scope, key, value: JSONB);

endif

stop

@enduml


