title <b>NextGenChat — Deployment Mode Strategy</b>\n<size:10>Security and infrastructure requirements scale incrementally. No breaking changes between modes.</size>

' ────────────────── MODE 1: LOCAL ──────────────────
package "MODE 1: LOCAL  (Current Focus)" #EFF8EF {
  component "**Runtime**\nDocker Compose\nlocalhost only" as M1a #CCEEBB
  component "**Users**\nSingle owner\n(setup wizard on first run)" as M1b #CCEEBB
  component "**Auth**\nJWT + Argon2id\nSetup wizard only\n(no registration)" as M1c #CCEEBB
  component "**TLS**\nHTTP only\n(localhost — no TLS needed)" as M1d #CCEEBB
  component "**API Keys**\nStored in .env\n(gitignored)" as M1e #CCEEBB
  component "**Rate Limiting**\nDisabled / relaxed\n(you = only user)" as M1f #CCEEBB
  component "**CORS**\nlocalhost origins\nonly" as M1g #CCEEBB
}

note bottom of M1a
  <b>All features available in LOCAL mode:</b>
  ✓ Full agent system (all 5 providers)
  ✓ Context management + compaction
  ✓ MCP integration
  ✓ File workspace + versioning
  ✓ Rules engine
  ✓ Cron / Heartbeat agents

  <b>Simplified in LOCAL mode:</b>
  • No email/SMTP required
  • No invite system
  • No rate limiting
  • API keys in .env (not encrypted DB)
  • No TLS configuration needed
  • Setup wizard replaces registration

  <b>DEPLOYMENT_MODE=local</b>
  in .env activates relaxed posture.
end note

' ────────────────── MODE 2: SHARED ──────────────────
package "MODE 2: SHARED  (Phase 7 — Friends)" #EEF0FF {
  component "**Runtime**\nVPS / Home Server\n+ Public Domain" as M2a #CCCCE8
  component "**Users**\nInvite-only\nregistration" as M2b #CCCCE8
  component "**Auth**\nJWT + Argon2id\n+ Email verification\n+ Password reset" as M2c #CCCCE8
  component "**TLS**\nRequired: Caddy\nauto Let's Encrypt\nHSTS preloaded" as M2d #CCCCE8
  component "**API Keys**\nAES-256-GCM\nencrypted in DB\n(not in .env)" as M2e #CCCCE8
  component "**Rate Limiting**\n100 req/min/IP\nper-endpoint limits\nFail2ban integration" as M2f #CCCCE8
  component "**CORS**\nExplicit domain\nallowlist only\n(no wildcard)" as M2g #CCCCE8
}

note bottom of M2a
  <b>Additions when switching to SHARED:</b>
  ✓ TLS mandatory (Caddy + Let's Encrypt)
  ✓ HSTS: max-age=31536000; preload
  ✓ Invite system enabled (signed JWT, 48h)
  ✓ Email/SMTP required (invites + reset)
  ✓ Rate limiting fully enforced
  ✓ CORS: explicit domain allowlist
  ✓ API keys moved to encrypted DB storage
  ✓ Friend data rights: GET /me/data
  ✓ Friend account delete: DELETE /me
  ✓ Owner revoke any session

  <b>Network options:</b>
  • Tailscale / WireGuard (recommended)
  • Reverse proxy to VPS
  • Cloudflare Tunnel

  <b>DEPLOYMENT_MODE=network</b>
  activates strict security posture.
end note

' ────────────────── MODE 3: MOBILE ──────────────────
package "MODE 3: MOBILE  (Phase 8)" #FFF8EF {
  component "**Runtime**\nExpo (iOS + Android)\nConnects to Mode 2" as M3a #F0D8B0
  component "**Token Storage**\nExpo SecureStore\n(hardware-backed)\nnever AsyncStorage" as M3b #F0D8B0
  component "**Network Security**\nCertificate pinning\n(MITM prevention)" as M3c #F0D8B0
  component "**Auth**\nBiometric unlock\n(FaceID / Fingerprint)\nlocal — not sent to server" as M3d #F0D8B0
  component "**Notifications**\nFCM + APNs\nNo content in payload\n(only channel name)" as M3e #F0D8B0
  component "**Sessions**\nDevice-bound tokens\n30-day expiry\nremote revocation" as M3f #F0D8B0
}

note bottom of M3a
  <b>Backend changes for MOBILE (additive only):</b>
  + POST /auth/mobile-token
    (device-bound, 30-day refresh token)
  + POST /push/register
    { deviceId, platform, fcmToken }
  + DELETE /push/unregister
    (called on logout)
  + DELETE /sessions/:deviceId
    (remote revoke — lost phone)
  + PushToken table in DB

  <b>No API contract changes.</b>
  Mobile is just another client —
  same Socket.io events, same REST API.
  Shared @nextgenchat/types package
  used by React Native via pnpm workspace.
end note

' ────────────────── MODE 4: CLOUD ──────────────────
package "MODE 4: CLOUD  (Phase 9+)" #FFF4F4 {
  component "**Runtime**\nKubernetes\nAuto-scaling pods" as M4a #EEBBB8
  component "**Database**\nManaged RDS\n+ PITR\n+ Read replicas" as M4b #EEBBB8
  component "**Cache / Queue**\nElastiCache\n(Redis managed)" as M4c #EEBBB8
  component "**File Storage**\nAWS S3\nCross-region replication" as M4d #EEBBB8
  component "**Secrets**\nHashiCorp Vault\nor AWS Secrets Manager" as M4e #EEBBB8
  component "**Observability**\nOTEL + Grafana\nLoki + Tempo\nPrometheus" as M4f #EEBBB8
}

note bottom of M4a
  <b>Cloud additions (no breaking changes):</b>
  ✓ PostgreSQL → Managed RDS (PITR enabled)
  ✓ Redis → ElastiCache
  ✓ MinIO → S3 (cross-region replication)
  ✓ Docker Compose → Kubernetes (HPA)
  ✓ PgBouncer connection pooling
  ✓ WAF + DDoS protection
  ✓ Audit log export for compliance
  ✓ Full OpenTelemetry tracing
  ✓ Grafana dashboards + alerts
    error rate > 1%, p95 > 2s,
    queue depth > 1000

  <b>RTO: < 4h | RPO: < 1h</b>
end note

' ────────────────── TRANSITIONS ──────────────────

note as NRule
  <b>Core rule:</b>
  Each mode transition is <b>additive only</b>.
  No breaking changes to DB schema or API contracts.
  DEPLOYMENT_MODE env var switches security posture:
  'local' = relaxed  |  'network' = strict
end note

M1a -right-> M2a : **Phase 7**\nAdd TLS + domain\ninvite system\nrate limiting
M2a -right-> M3a : **Phase 8**\nMobile is another\nclient — same API
M3a -right-> M4a : **Phase 9+**\nKubernetes +\nmanaged infra

@enduml
